<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,324,678,704]" box="[189,324,678,704]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,678,704]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,678,704]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,1398,725,822]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
The species is named in honour of our colleague Dr Krystyna Saunders (Australian Nuclear Science and Technology Organisation, Kirrawee, 
<collectingCountry box="[681,791,760,787]" name="Australia" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Australia</collectingCountry>
) to acknowledge her for her ecological and paleoecological diatom research on the sub-Antarctic islands in the Pacific Ocean.
</paragraph>
